  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Beauty and Wellness Sales Consultant/Manager",
  "description": "<h2><strong>Job Requirements</strong></h2><ol><li><p>Minimum <strong>2 years of relevant experience</strong> in <strong>Beauty</strong>, <strong>Wellness</strong>, and <strong>retail/outlet management</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Strong communication skills in both <strong>English and Mandarin</strong>, to liaise effectively with English-speaking clients and Mandarin-speaking colleagues/customers.</p></li><li><p>Possess <strong>leadership qualities</strong>, initiative, and a positive, team-oriented attitude.</p></li><li><p>Comfortable working on <strong>retail hours</strong>, including weekends and public holidays.<br /><br /><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ol><li><p>Oversee and manage the <strong>daily operations</strong> of the outlet to ensure smooth and efficient performance.</p></li><li><p><strong>Lead, motivate, and guide team members</strong>, fostering a culture of professionalism and excellence.</p></li><li><p>Maintain and uphold the <strong>highest standards of service quality</strong> in line with the company’s brand values.</p></li><li><p>Deliver <strong>exceptional customer service</strong>, building trust and long-term relationships with clients.</p></li><li><p>Attend to customer inquiries and provide <strong>professional consultation</strong> on suitable treatments and products.</p></li><li><p>Monitor and manage <strong>customer records, purchases, and treatment history</strong> accurately.</p></li><li><p>Conduct <strong>follow-ups on post-treatment experiences</strong> to ensure customer satisfaction and retention.</p></li><li><p>Drive <strong>sales performance</strong> by promoting treatment packages and products.</p></li><li><p>Perform necessary <strong>administrative and reporting tasks</strong>, as required by management.</p></li><li><p>Carry out <strong>ad hoc duties</strong> assigned by the management team.</p></li></ol></li></ol><p></p>",
